 MBOMBELA –Hawks spokesman Capt Dineo Sekgotodi said  Malwane was arrested on May 2, at N4 Nkomazi Toll Plaza following a disruptive operation by the Hawks’ team after information was received about a Toyota Hilux bakkie that was reportedly transporting illicit goods. ALSO READ: Tips to prevent becoming a victim of cybercrime “The vehicle was stopped and searched resulting in 1 242 counterfeit Adidas tracksuits were found and confiscated, Malwane was then arrested on the spot.” ALSO READ: Barberton no longer jewel of the Lowveld The court sentenced Malwane to R30 000.00 or 48 months imprisonment, wholly suspended for 3 years. The vehicle used in the commission of crime has been forfeited to the state.